The rules have been effect for the last year or so with additional clarifications added.<br>
<br>
Enclosed is the following revised Schedule.<br>
Any questions please ask them in advance.<br>
No one wants to be running over each other<br>
in NTOV.<br>
<br>
ToS and ToN  have Dropped from the rotation<br>
<br>
Inconcievable(INC) and Guardians of Light(GOL)<br>
have been added<br>
<br>
Since ToN will be leaving the Rotation I need a<br>
reliable Person to Maintain the schedule. Please<br>
let me know if you are interested.<br>
<br>
Clairification;<br>
Ikathar, Sont and Eashen has never been considered<br>
part of the Rotation. Rotation guilds can and do<br>
kill them to clear the way into Arry, etc but any guild<br>
that gets there FiF can bag em.<br>
<br>
If you have any concerns with the current<br>
setup of this agreement - please state it<br>
and distribute to the mailing list.<br>
<br>
June 30 Isen<br>
July 7  FS<br>
July 14 FotC<br>
July 21 Raven Nest<br>
July 28 INC<br>
Aug   4 GOL<br>
Aug  11 Isen<br>
Aug  18 FS<br>
Aug  25 FotC<br>
<br>
Rules as currently defined:<br>
- When Aaryonar spawns, you have 24 hours to kill<br>
him. If he spawns at 1am EST, you have until 1am EST<br>
the following day, otherwise it becomes open to<br>
anyone.<br>
- if there is a patch - that guild gets lucky<br>
- Week runs from Monday 0000 to Sunday 2400<br>
- This is NOT liscense to Kill all the Uber mobs<br>
in the game and THEN come back for Aary. You kill a<br>
Major Mob while Arry is up, you forfiet.<br>
<br>
- After killing Aaryonar, you must kill mobs in<br>
NToV, or relinquish any claim on them. If mobs are up in<br>
NToV, and you leave NToV to raid then it becomes<br>
open to anyone. Raid size mobs are one that require 18<br>
players or more. This means if your guild were to<br>
opt to do Yelinak, and Lady Nev was up, then you would<br>
forfeit any rights to her by raiding another mob.<br>
You not in NTOV for 48 hours, then it become open<br>
to anyone.<br>
<br>
Thanks and good hunting<br>
 <p>Tose<BR><br>
Guild Leader - <br>
Travelers of Norrath<BR><br>
